Mouth terminal. Two rows of premaxillary teeth (
Fig. 2
); outer row with 0(1), 1(1), 2(5), 3(33) or 4*(40) teeth with three cusps, median cusps longer; inner row with 4(7), 5*(66), 6(7) or 7(1) teeth with five to seven cusps. Maxillary with 1(1), 2*(56), 3(23) or 4(1) teeth three to five cusps. Dentary with 4*(49) or 5(32) teeth with five to seven cups, followed by 0(3), 2(1), 3(4), 4(9), 5(17), 6*(19), 7(19), 8(6) or 9(3) smaller teeth with one to five cusps.
